RIYADH: The Saudi Cabinet affirmed its keenness to support international efforts to reach a political solution in Yemen during its weekly meeting on Tuesday, according to the Saudi Press Agency. The cabinet reiterated the Kingdom's keenness to support efforts made by the United Nations to reach a sustainable political solution to the Yemeni crisis, as well as to alleviate the suffering of the brotherly Yemeni people. The session was chaired by Saudi King Salman this Tuesday afternoon at the Al-Salam Palace in Jeddah.